R=M_n(\mathbb{Q})
E \in M_n(\mathbb{Q})
R=M_n(\mathbb{Q})
\exists 
E' \in M_n(\mathbb{Q})
EE'=E'E=I_n
E
det(E) \neq 0
$$ $E \in M_n(\mathbb{Q})$ is an unit of the ring $R=M_n(\mathbb{Q})$,if $\exists $ $E' \in M_n(\mathbb{Q})$ such that $EE'=E'E=I_n$,that means that $E$ must be inversible.So,$det(E) \neq 0$. 
